- "Top customers" refers to those who have spent the most money;
- "Total spending" is the sum of the total values of all orders placed by a customer;
- "Orders placed" is the count of orders a customer has made;
- "Returns" is the count of items a customer has returned.

- "Perfect fit" refers to clothing items with a bust measurement between 80-85 cm and 90-95 cm;
- "About to go on sale soon" means the discount period starts within the next 30 days;
- "Single available size" means the item has only one size option.

- 'Most profitable' refers to the highest total revenue;
- 'Current inventory level' is the quantity of the item in stock;
- 'Average customer rating' is the average of all ratings given by customers for the item.

- "loyal patrons" refers to customers who have placed more than one order;
- "woven a tapestry of multiple purchases" refers to customers who have made multiple orders;
- "spending more than $100 in total" is the condition for the total amount spent by the customer;
- "finest threads" refers to the clothing items purchased;
- "value of each thread" refers to the total value of each order.

- 'Top 3 best-selling items' refers to the items with the highest total sales in each category;
- 'Total sales' is calculated as the sum of the quantities sold for each item;
- The ranking is done within each category separately.

- Total discount is calculated by summing the discount percentages for each item;
- Average review rating is calculated by averaging the ratings given by customers for each item;
- The query selects the top item based on these two metrics.

- "Garments" refers to clothing items;
- "Woven the most gold into their threads" refers to the highest total revenue generated;
- "Claimed by the eager masses" refers to the total number of items ordered;
- "Class" refers to the category of the clothing items;
- The results are ordered by the total revenue in descending order.

- 'XXS' is a size designation for very small clothing items;
- '10%' discount means the price is reduced by 10%;
- 'November 2023' refers to the period from November 1, 2023, to November 30, 2023.

"Multiple times" refers to items with at least 3 reviews;
"Most ordered items" are those with the highest total quantity;
"Highest average ratings" are the items with the best average review scores.
